-- Wi-Lan sues RIM for patent infringement
-- 
-- Mon Jan 23, 2012 8:26am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/01/23/us-wilan-idUSTRE80M0ZB20120123

 

 (Reuters) - Patent licensing company Wi-Lan said it has sued Research In Motion for infringing on its patents. 
 The company said it filed a suit in the U.S. District Court for the Southern District of Florida against the BlackBerry maker. Wi-LAN, which has licensed its intellectual property to over 255 companies worldwide, alleged RIM infringed its U.S. Patent No. 5,515,369 and U.S. Patent No. 6,232,969. (Reporting by  Krishna N Das  in Bangalore; Editing by Sriraj Kalluvila)